The paper also discusses the use of various automata models, such as Visibly Pushdown Automata and Synchronized Automata, which are related to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of operator precedence, which is related to the sub-category cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the closure properties of these languages, which is related to the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages).
